# Game modal dialogs — simulation pause

When you **add or wire a new modal dialog** in the game client (new `*Dialog` component, new `*DialogOpen` / dialog slice on the store, or mounting a dialog in `GameContainer` / `pages/game.tsx`), STOP and run this checklist before finishing.

## Step 0 — Decide blocking vs non-blocking (default = blocking)

**Should the world freeze while it is open?** If the player should not advance production, play time, random events, or attack-wave timers — or should not have a **second dialog (event/combat/etc.) appear stacked on top** — it is **blocking**.

Default to **blocking** for anything that overlays gameplay. Only treat a dialog as non-blocking if it is a tiny, purely informational popover where stacking and time passing are genuinely fine.

## Step 1 — Open flag MUST live in the Zustand store (not local `useState`)

A blocking dialog's open flag has to be readable by the game loop. If you keep it in component `useState`, the loop cannot see it, so **the sim keeps running and other dialogs stack over yours** (this is the exact bug to avoid). Wire the flag through the store:

- Add `xxxDialogOpen: boolean` to the `GameStore` interface and `setXxxDialogOpen: (isOpen: boolean) => void`.
- Default it to `false` in the store initializer and in the restart/reset state.
- Implement the setter with `set({ xxxDialogOpen: isOpen })`.
- In components, read/write it via the store — do **not** use local `useState` for a blocking dialog.

(Mirror an existing flag like `deleteAccountDialogOpen` end-to-end as a template.)

## Step 2 — Add it to the modal-pause SSOT (if blocking)

Add the flag to the OR-chain in **`isBlockingDialogOpen`** (which feeds `isNonRewardBlockingModalOpen` → `isModalDialogOpen`) in `client/src/game/state.ts`. That chain is the **only** place to list blocking modal flags; `isModalDialogOpen` adds `rewardDialog` on top. Do **not** re-list dialogs in `loop.ts`.

## Step 3 — Mark it UI-only so it is never persisted

Add the property to **`UI_ONLY_PROPERTIES`** in `client/src/game/stateHelpers.ts` and to **`getTransientDialogResetOnLoad`** (so a stale `true` from any save can never freeze the sim on load). For nested UI-only slices, list under an object already covered.

## Step 4 — If you chose non-blocking

Skip `isModalDialogOpen`, and briefly document in code/PR **why** time passing and a stacked event dialog are acceptable.

## When editing an existing dialog

Re-check whether it became blocking (or should be removed from `isBlockingDialogOpen` / `isModalDialogOpen`), and whether its flag moved between local state and the store.
